SUMMARY:Eskenazi Museum of Art: After Hours at the Museum 2026
DESCRIPTION:Enjoy a special after-hours experience at the renowned Sidney
  and Lois Eskenazi Museum of Art at Indiana University at the After Hours
  at the Museum Fundraiser. Come for an evening of outdoor live music\, de
 licious food and drinks\, and immersive art experiences inside the museum
 . Bring a friend\, come curious\, and feel good knowing your ticket suppo
 rts the community's art museum.Outdoor highlights: Spend a summer evening
  on the museum's front lawn with food\, drinks\, art-making\, and live mu
 sic by the&#160\;Quinn Sternberg Quartet.Indoor highlights: Explore the g
 alleries at your own pace and step into our featured exhibition\, Mulyana
 : Vital Ecosystems\, where vibrant installations transform the space into
  a colorful underwater seascape.Match Challenge! Thanks to the generosity
  of museum friend Chris Morrow\, we are also thrilled to announce a $50\,
 000 match challenge. Whether you purchase tickets for yourself and a frie
 nd or choose to make an additional donation\, every dollar will be matche
 dŌĆödoubling the impact of your support for the museum.  To reserve your 
 spot\, register now and make a payment via credit card.Individual Ticket:
  $75  Charitable portion $50 | Value of benefits received $25 (food and b
 everage)  Are you under the age of 40? Use the promotion code UNDER40 for
  $25 off the ticket price.Under 40 Individual Ticket: $50  Charitable por
 tion $25 | Value of benefits received $25 (food and beverage)  We look fo
 rward to celebrating with you at this special event!  Questions?  Contact
  Elliott Deatrick at edeatri@iu.edu (mailto:edeatri@iu.edu) or 812-856-31
 12.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Enjoy a special after-hours experience 
 at the renowned Sidney and Lois Eskenazi Museum of Art at Indiana Univers
 ity at the <strong>After Hours at the Museum Fundraiser</strong>. Come fo
 r an evening of outdoor live music\, delicious food and drinks\, and imme
 rsive art experiences inside the museum. Bring a friend\, come curious\, 
 and feel good knowing your ticket supports the community's art museum.</p
 ><p><span style="text-decoration: underline\;">Outdoor highlights</span>:
  Spend a summer evening on the museum's front lawn with food\, drinks\, a
 rt-making\, and live music by the&#160\;<em>Quinn Sternberg Quartet</em>.
 </p><p><span style="text-decoration: underline\;">Indoor highlights</span
 >: Explore the galleries at your own pace and step into our featured exhi
 bition\, <em>Mulyana: Vital Ecosystems</em>\, where vibrant installations
  transform the space into a colorful underwater seascape.</p><p><strong>M
 atch Challenge!</strong> Thanks to the generosity of museum friend Chris 
 Morrow\, we are also thrilled to announce a $50\,000 match challenge. Whe
 ther you purchase tickets for yourself and a friend or choose to make an 
 additional donation\, every dollar will be matchedŌĆö<em>doubling the imp
 act</em> of your support for the museum.</p><p>  To reserve your spot\, r
 egister now and make a payment via credit card.<br /><span style="text-de
 coration: underline\;">Individual Ticket</span>: $75<br />  Charitable po
 rtion $50 | Value of benefits received $25 (food and beverage)</p><p>  Ar
 e you under the age of 40? Use the promotion code UNDER40 for $25 off the
  ticket price.<br /><span style="text-decoration: underline\;">Under 40 I
 ndividual Ticket</span>: $50<br />  Charitable portion $25 | Value of ben
 efits received $25 (food and beverage)</p><p>  We look forward to celebra
 ting with you at this special event!</p><p>  Questions?<br />  Contact <s
 trong>Elliott Deatrick</strong> at <a title="Eskenazi Museum of Art: Afte
 r Hours at the Museum 2026" href="mailto:edeatri@iu.edu" target="_blank" 
 rel="noopener">edeatri@iu.edu</a> or 812-856-3112.</p>
