SUMMARY:Writing in the Galleries
DESCRIPTION:In this workshop\, we begin by looking closely at artworkŌĆöa
 sking what we see\, think\, feel\, and wonder. Together\, we'll explore w
 hat we think the artist is trying to say and what the social significance
  of their message might be. Then we'll use our imaginations to respond to
  any aspect of our experience. Poets\, story-tellers\, and essayists are 
 all welcome in this group!  What to Bringyour favorite pencil (no pens). 
  a notebook or paper. Clipboards are available to borrow.  a phone or cam
 era to take a picture of the art for later reference.  Know Before You Go
 Arrive early\, check in\, and get ready for an on-time start.Readwhere to
  find us\, where to park\, accessibility\, and museum guidelines.About Yo
 ur Facilitator  Dedaimia Whitney earned an MFA in fiction from Indiana Un
 iversity under the direction of Scott Russell Sanders. She taught creativ
 e writing at Franklin College for many years. She has served the museum a
 s a docent since 2019. Her favorite works of art are those that are both 
 visually stimulating and thought-provoking.
