LOCATION:SIDNEY AND LOIS ESKENAZI MUSEUM OF ART - Room Number: Rhoem Fami
 ly Art Making Studio
GEO:39.169144;-86.519739
SUMMARY:Family Art Lab
DESCRIPTION:Designed for K-12 students and their families\, this event of
 fers a fun and flexible way to spark creativity and connect with each oth
 er. All ages and experience levels are welcome!  Come and go at your own 
 pace. We recommend planning for at least an hour to explore the gallery a
 nd make art.  Start in the Art Studio inside the Kimberly and John Simpso
 n Center for Education on the museum's 2nd floor to pick up your Gallery 
 Challenge. Then head to the galleries to find the artwork we'll use as in
 spiration for our project! When you're ready\, head back to the studio fo
 r our hands-on art-making activity that everyone will love.  This program
  takes place every Second Sunday of the month\, excluding holidays and mu
 seum closures. Each month features new artworks and materials\, so there'
 s always something fresh to explore and create!  All children must be cha
 peroned.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Designed for K-12 students and their fa
 milies\, this event offers a fun and flexible way to spark creativity and
  connect with each other. All ages and experience levels are welcome!</p>
 <p>  Come and go at your own pace. We recommend planning for at least an 
 hour to explore the gallery and make art.</p><p>  Start in the Art Studio
  inside the Kimberly and John Simpson Center for Education on the museum'
 s 2nd floor to pick up your Gallery Challenge. Then head to the galleries
  to find the artwork we'll use as inspiration for our project! When you'r
 e ready\, head back to the studio for our hands-on art-making activity th
 at everyone will love.</p><p>  This program takes place every Second Sund
 ay of the month\, excluding holidays and museum closures. Each month feat
 ures new artworks and materials\, so there's always something fresh to ex
 plore and create!</p><p>  All children must be chaperoned.</p>
